Meet <b>littledottie</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Littledottie lives at <a href='/home/?user=littlrdottie'>2199 Pine Road</a> in the quiet, historical neighborhood of Ravenwood. She fell for the old architecture when she moved to Millsberry on September 26, 2004, and has made herself a comfortable home there over the past two years. <br><br>Littledottie has a flair for the creative and a wide range of interests. Her home is very carefully planned and furnished, and it's clear she has a great eye for color and design. She also enjoys magic tricks, and spends part of her week practicing new tricks to add to her routine. And there's nothing that gets her more in the mood for magic than keeping track of the strange happenings at nearby Red Lion Manor. She's been recording her observations on her computer, one of her most prized possessions. With all these inquisitive and clever thoughts running through her head, we hope she's submitted some work to the art contest! <br><br>When she's not exploring her neighborhood, littledottie lounges around with her pets or hangs out with friends, talking about school, clothes, and music (pop, rap, and reggae). She may seem shy at first, but once you get to know her she's totally friendly and will keep you on your toes with her great energy and ideas. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, littledottie, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
